<answer\Pascal's triangle is a triangular array of the binomial coefficients. The $n$th diagonal of the triangle is given by the formula $d_n = \binom{n}{r}$ for $r = 0, 1, \ldots, n$. The sum of the squares of the diagonal elements is given by
\[\sum_{n\geq 0} d_n^2 = \sum_{n\geq 0} \binom{n}{r}^2 = \frac{1}{r!(n-r)!}\sum_{n\geq 0} n! = \frac{1}{r!}\sum_{n\geq 0} \binom{n}{r}n! = \frac{1}{r!}\sum_{n\geq 0} \frac{n!}{(n-r)!} = \frac{1}{r!}\sum_{n\geq 0} \frac{n!}{n!(n-r)!} = \frac{1}{r!}\sum_{n\geq 0} \frac{1}{(n-r)!} = \frac{1}{r!}\sum_{n\geq 0} e^n = \frac{1}{r!}\frac{1}{1-e}.\end{answer}

